n   - Minimum level: Unit\n   - Plan consistent: Yes (CONCATENATE is a function)\n   - Level probabilities: {Unit: 0.90, Integration: 0.08, System: 0.01, Agentic: 0.01, Workflow: 0.0}\n\n7. **Cross-sheet formula reference resolution**\n   - Description: Formulas referencing cells in different sheets resolve correctly when the referenced sheet exists and contains the expected values.\n   - Justification: Tests cross-sheet reference resolution, which is deterministic formula evaluation logic.\n   - Test description: Create formulas that reference cells across sheets, verify they resolve to the correct values, and test behavior when references are invalid.\n   - Minimum level: Unit\n   - Plan consistent: Yes (formula resolution is in-process)\n   - Level probabilities: {Unit: 0.85, Integration: 0.12, System: 0.02, Agentic: 0.01, Workflow: 0.0}\n\n8. **Dependent formula recalculation in topological order**\n   - Description: When a cell's value changes, all dependent formulas recalculate in the correct topological order to avoid stale values.\n   - Justification: Tests dependency graph construction and recalculation propagation logic. Failures would manifest as formulas using outdated values or recalculating in the wrong sequence.\n   - Test description: Set up a chain of dependent formulas, change a base cell value, and verify all dependents recalculate in the correct order with updated values.\n   - Minimum level: Unit\n   - Plan consistent: Yes (recalculation is deterministic)\n   - Level probabilities: {Unit: 0.80, Integration: 0.15, System: 0.03, Agentic: 0.01, Workflow: 0.01}\n\n9. **Undo operation restores formula and dependent values**\n   - The undo mechanism must fully restore both the original formula and all cascading dependent cell values, not just one or the other. Setting up interconnected cells, modifying a formula, and undoing it verifies the undo stack and storage layer work together correctly.\n   - Test description: Build cells with formulas and dependencies. Edit a formula (e.g., change B1 from =A1*2 to =A1*3, which causes C1 to recalculate). Trigger undo. Assert the formula text reverts and all dependent values return to their prior state.\n   - Minimum level: Integration\n   - Plan consistent: Yes (validates complete state restoration across the undo workflow)\n   - Level probabilities: {Unit: 0.12, Integration: 0.81, System: 0.03, Agentic: 0.01, Workflow: 0.03}\n\n10. **Workbook persistence and loading**\n    - Saving and reloading a workbook must preserve all cell values, formulas, and floating-point precision without corruption or loss. This tests the serialization and deserialization layers, which can fail in ways like formula loss, precision degradation, or dependent values not being written to disk. Real file I/O is necessary to catch bugs in the disk format and file handling.\n    - Test description: Create a workbook with formulas, values, and dependencies. Serialize it to a file.\n    - Deserialize from the file and verify all cell values, formulas, and precision match the original. Optionally check binary format integrity.\n    - Minimum level: System\n    - Plan consistent: Yes (tests actual file I/O)\n    - Level probabilities: {Unit: 0.02, Integration: 0.12, System: 0.84, Agentic: 0.01, Workflow: 0.01}\n\nVerifying the probability distributions sum correctly across all test cases. Each set of level probabilities adds to 1.0, confirming the allocations are valid. Now formatting the final output.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13520,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13520},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"73fcf831-886a-47d2-a25c-f03d704b7a34","uuid":"8ae4f68f-d2a2-4587-b6d2-af5a17830f48"}
